    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ring-shaped extrusions or objects that are positioned below the opening of a bottle or other vessel from which a liquid is poured, on a candlestick or other object, with the purpose of impeding or stopping drips of the liquid from running down the body of the vessel. For drip catchers on candlesticks, use "bobeches."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
